        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-08 20:34:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\nGood work Charles!   Some feedback, since ueb, and dmaap are part of the drools-pdp infrastructure.   It is best to move just this simulator under the drools-pdp.\n\nI expect policy-endpoints in drools-pdp junits beefed up considerably now that there would be simulator.   So, a subsequent step after this work, would be to beef up the junits in the drools-pdp side.\n\nBut drools-pdp should not depend on drools-applications, therefore this work is best to be moved in the drools-pdp repo.\n\nIdeally this can be a simulators feature in the drools pdp.   Hopefully the feature can be used both ways: a) simulator, and b) junits.  One consideration is then circular dependencies, I wonder if that could be avoided setting the maven-surefire-plugin classpath entries.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
